-------BASICS-------

date : Displays date in UTC format

ls : List all files in the current directory
ls -l : Detailed view of all files

pwd : Current working directory path

mkdir : creates new working directory

touch <filename> : creates a new file

cd : change directory
cd .. : previous path

rm <filename> : remove file

rm -r <directory name> : remove files recursively

rmdir <directory name> : removes directory

cat <filename> : displays content in the file

echo "text" : prints content on the screen

echo "text" > filename : Adds the text to file if file exists or creates a new file

head -n 5 <filename> : Displays first 5 lines

tail -n 5 <filenmae> : displays last 5 lines

tail -f <filename> : Displays new logs adding to the file

less <filename> : paginated view of file

more <filename> : more pages

-------------------

cp sourcefile destinationpath : copying files

cp -r source destination : recursive copying

mv source destination : moving files

mv filename newfilename : rename files

wc filename : word count of the file  

ln -s /path/file softlink-file : Create softlink in the present directory

ln /path/file hardlink-file : Create hardlink in the present directory

cut -b 1-4 filename: Gives a small portion from the file

echo "Hello" | tee file : Prints and puts content in the file

sort filename : sorts contents

clear : clears the screen

diff file1 file2 : Difference between two files

wc file1 file2 file3 : Displays word count in each files

vi/vim filename : text editor where we can edit files with advanced features.

-------------------

ssh-keygen : creates public and private keys

Disk Usage

df -h : disk usage

du . : disk utility

Processes

top -h : processes running

ps : process id

fuser : file system user (Network Attached Storage)

kill -9 processid : kills a process

free -h : Shows Disk space

nohup free -h : Stores logs in nohup.out and adds on next

vmstat -a : Displays virtual memory(RAM)

-------------------

System Level Commands

uname : Displays which platform

uptime : How long system is runing in UTC

who : displays list of users logged in and for how long

whoami : current user 

which : displays location of the command

id : Displays uid,gid,groups of the users

sudo : super user do - root user has all permission (sudo is a group)

cat /etc/passwd : list of users

sudo shutdown : shutdowns the system

sudo reboot : resboots the system

apt : application package manager for ubuntu

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install docker.io
sudo apt remove docker.io

yum : application package manager for CentOS

dnf : application package manager for Fedora

pacman : application package manager for Arch Linux

portage : application package manager for Gentoo Linux

rpm : application package manager for RedHat

-------------------

User & Group management commands

sudo useradd -m username : User will be created in /home/

sudo passwd username : Adds password to user

su username : switches user

sudo userdel username : Deletes user

sudo groupadd groupname : Creates groups

cat /etc/group : Displays list of groups

sudo gpasswd -a username groupname : Adds user to a group

sudo gpasswd -M user1,user2,user3 groupname : Adds multiple users to a group

sudo groupdel groupname : Deletes group


-------------------

File permission commands

ls -l : List the contents in the directory with permissions

r-read w-write x-execute

---  0
--x  1
-w-  2
-wx  3
r--  4
r-x  5
rw-  6
rwx  7

chmod 777 filename : changes permissions according to the above value

umask : Default permission of a newly added file

sudo chown username filename : change ownership

sudo chgrp groupname filename : change group

-------------------

Compression commands

sudo apt install zip

zip -r file.zip filename : zips a file into a filename with zip extension

unzip file.zip : unzip a file

tar -cvzf filename.tar.gz filename : compresses file in tar

tar -xvzf filename.tar.gz destination : extract tar files in destination

